definitions.definition: An island and country in the Mediterranean Sea , normally considered politically part of Southeast Europe but geographically part of Western Asia . Official name: Republic of Cyprus . Capital: Nicosia .
A suburban area of Beckton , borough of Newham , Greater London , England , named after the Mediterranean island ( OS grid ref TQ4380 ) .
